{
  "texts": [
    "The model has not connected the countries class with the reference in the natural language question.",
    "It has also not made use of the information in the ontology that shows that the classes car_makers and countries are connected.",
    "For this type of error, the model chooses the wrong variable for an aggregation.",
    "Example 14 in the Appendix is syntactically correct, however, since the variable?T1_petid does not exist in any of the triples in the query, the query returns an empty set.",
    "The natural language question for Example 15 in the Appendix is \"how many cars were produced in 1980?\"."
  ]
}